« and »writing facts«, the volume shows why and how »facts« are a result of knowledge, rules, and norms as well as of description, argumentation, and narration. This approach allows new perspectives »fact« and its impact on modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCivilization, Modern. 0aFacts (Philosophy). 4aArts. 4aBritish Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 4aLanguage. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aMedia. 4aSociety. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aArts.  aBritish Studies.  aCultural Studies.  aLanguage.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedia.  aSociety.1 aAlbrecht, Kristin Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandt, Stefan L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuber, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöfler, Elke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIbing, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnaller, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnaller, Susanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMartínez Márquez, Iyari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Harro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNünning, Ansgar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPany-Habsa, Doris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRieger, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoedern, Gero von, econtributor.4ct